==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-chump.ogg|Audio (US)}}

=== Noun ===
'''chump''' (''plural'' '''chumps''')
# (''U.S. Slang'') the opposite of a champ; a [[loser]]
# the smaller of two [[bully|bullies]]
#: ''I'll take on that '''chump''', and you fight the other one.''
# {{slang}} derogatory term describing a loser, or a spoilsport.
#:''Oh man, You are such a '''chump'''.''
# a foolish or gullible person; a sucker; someone easily taken advantage of
#:''It shouldn't be hard to put one over on ''that'' '''chump'''.''
# one with compunctions which disallow taking advantage dishonestly or unfairly (used by the unscrupulous to describe the scrupulous; thus:) a fool
#:''What a '''chump'''!  He could have kept that money!  Who would have known?''

